    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>People called on for professional advice or services regarding matters in the field of their special knowledge or training, usually for specific projects or problems. For persons who give advice either professionally or nonprofessionally, usually on an ongoing basis, use "advisors."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000050615/IFLA Glossary for Art Librarians (1984)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para personas visitadas para consejo profesional o servicios relativos a materias en el campo de su conocimiento o capacitación especial, usualmente para proyectos específicos o problemas. Para personas que dan consejo tanto profesional como no profesional, usualmente en una base continua, use "asesor".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Te gebruiken voor personen die om professioneel advies of diensten worden gevraagd, meestal voor specifieke projecten of problemen, gerelateerd aan hun specifieke kennis of specialisatie.  Gebruik 'adviseurs' voor personen die meestal op lopende basis advies geven op professionele of niet-professionele wijze.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>對於針對特定計畫或問題，被請來提供其領域內專精知識或訓練之專業建議者。對於通常持續提供專業或非專業建議者，則使用「顧問(advisors)」一詞。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
